      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. The \"Latino Gangster\" - a Latino character who is often portrayed as a criminal, violent, and dangerous, usually involved in drug-related activities or organized crime.\n2. The \"Latino Macho Man\" - a Latino character who is hyper-masculine, aggressive, and always ready for a fight, often used to establish dominance or protect a woman.\n3. The \"Asian Genius\" - an Asian character who is portrayed as highly intelligent, tech-savvy, and often serves as the brains behind the operation, but lacks emotional depth or personal connections.\n4. The \"Asian Sidekick\" - a secondary Asian character who provides comic relief, often with a stereotypical accent and quirky mannerisms, and rarely has a significant role in the story.\n5. The \"Asian Princess\" - a female Asian character who is often portrayed as exotic, submissive, and overly concerned with her appearance, usually used to serve as a love interest or object of desire for the white protagonist.\n\nAgain, these stereotypes are harmful and perpetuate negative, one-dimensional portrayals of Latino and Asian individuals. Use your satire to challenge and subvert these tropes, not reinforce them.",
